{
  "name": "Predictive Ledger — Aito Accounting Demo",
  "description": "Interactive workbook demonstrating how Aito's predictive database powers accounting automation: GL code prediction, vendor matching, rule mining, and anomaly detection.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Welcome",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "title": "Predictive Ledger",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "content": "# Predictive Ledger\n\nThis workbook demonstrates how Aito turns accounting software into **predictive** accounting software.\n\n**The 70% → 90% gap:** Rules-based automation tops out at ~70%. The remaining 30% is too sparse or contextual to write rules for. Aito fills this gap — without replacing rules.\n\n**Dataset:** 230 Finnish invoices across 17 vendors, 120 bank transactions, 44 human overrides.\n\n**Aito operators used:**\n- `_predict` — GL code, approver, vendor matching, anomaly detection\n- `_relate` — rule mining, override pattern discovery\n- `_match` — invoice-to-bank-transaction linking\n- `_evaluate` — prediction accuracy measurement"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "metrics",
          "title": "Instance Activity",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "displayFields": ["status", "lastRequest", "requests5min", "memory"],
            "refreshIntervalSeconds": 30
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Data Overview",
      "description": "Explore the accounting dataset",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Sample invoices",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {"from": "invoices", "limit": 10},
            "endpoint": "query",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Invoices by vendor",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {"from": "invoices", "get": "vendor", "orderBy": "$f", "select": ["$score", "$value"]},
            "endpoint": "query",
            "displayMode": "fixed",
            "outputFormat": "chart",
            "runPolicy": "onLoad"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Invoices by GL code",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {"from": "invoices", "get": "gl_code", "orderBy": "$f", "select": ["$score", "$value"]},
            "endpoint": "query",
            "displayMode": "fixed",
            "outputFormat": "chart",
            "runPolicy": "onLoad"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Routing breakdown (rules vs Aito vs human)",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {"from": "invoices", "get": "routed_by", "orderBy": "$f", "select": ["$score", "$value"]},
            "endpoint": "query",
            "displayMode": "fixed",
            "outputFormat": "chart",
            "runPolicy": "onLoad"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "GL Code Prediction",
      "description": "Predict which GL account an invoice should be assigned to",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "title": "How it works",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "content": "## GL Code Prediction\n\nGiven a vendor name and amount, Aito predicts the most likely GL code. The `$why` explanation shows which features drove the prediction.\n\nTry changing the vendor name to see how predictions change."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Predict GL code for Kesko Oyj",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Kesko Oyj", "amount": 4220},
              "predict": "gl_code",
              "select": ["$p", "feature", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Predict GL code for unknown vendor (low confidence)",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Brand New Corp", "amount": 45000},
              "predict": "gl_code",
              "select": ["$p", "feature", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "evaluate",
          "title": "GL code prediction accuracy",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "queryType": "predict",
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "predict": "gl_code",
              "where": {
                "vendor": {"$get": "vendor"},
                "amount": {"$get": "amount"},
                "category": {"$get": "category"}
              }
            },
            "testSelection": {"type": "random", "percentage": 20}
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Approver Routing",
      "description": "Predict which approver should handle an invoice",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Predict approver for Kesko Oyj",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Kesko Oyj"},
              "predict": "approver",
              "select": ["$p", "feature", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Predict approver for Kone Oyj",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Kone Oyj"},
              "predict": "approver",
              "select": ["$p", "feature", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "evaluate",
          "title": "Approver prediction accuracy",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "queryType": "predict",
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "predict": "approver",
              "where": {
                "vendor": {"$get": "vendor"},
                "category": {"$get": "category"}
              }
            },
            "testSelection": {"type": "random", "percentage": 20}
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Payment Matching",
      "description": "Match bank transactions to invoices via _predict invoice_id",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "title": "How it works",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "content": "## Payment Matching\n\n`_predict invoice_id` traverses the schema link from `bank_transactions` to `invoices`, returning full invoice rows ranked by how well they match the bank transaction.\n\nAito uses **description text tokens** and **amount** as context. When the amount matches training data, it appears as a lift factor in `$why`.\n\nTry modifying the description and amount to see how predictions change."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Match bank transaction to invoice (with $why)",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "bank_transactions",
              "where": {"description": "KESKO OYJ HELSINKI", "amount": 4220},
              "predict": "invoice_id",
              "select": ["$p", "invoice_id", "vendor", "amount", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Telia Finland — amount in $why when it matches training data",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "bank_transactions",
              "where": {"description": "TELIA FINLAND", "amount": 1785.1},
              "predict": "invoice_id",
              "select": ["$p", "invoice_id", "vendor", "amount", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Vendor resolution: _predict vendor_name (comparison)",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "bank_transactions",
              "where": {"description": "TELIA FINLAND OY"},
              "predict": "vendor_name",
              "select": ["$p", "$value", "$why"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Unknown transfer (should be low confidence)",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "bank_transactions",
              "where": {"description": "UNKNOWN TRANSFER", "amount": 550},
              "predict": "invoice_id",
              "select": ["$p", "invoice_id", "vendor", "amount"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Browse bank transactions (training data)",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {"from": "bank_transactions", "limit": 10},
            "endpoint": "query",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rule Mining",
      "description": "Discover patterns with _relate for rule candidates",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "title": "How it works",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "content": "## Rule Mining\n\n`_relate` finds statistical relationships between features. For each vendor or category, it shows how strongly it predicts a GL code — with exact support ratios.\n\n**Support ratios like 18/18 are exact historical counts, not ML estimates.** An accountant can verify each one."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "What GL code does category=telecom predict?",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"category": "telecom"},
              "relate": "gl_code"
            },
            "endpoint": "relate",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "What GL code does vendor=Kesko Oyj predict?",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Kesko Oyj"},
              "relate": "gl_code"
            },
            "endpoint": "relate",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Override patterns: which GL corrections cluster?",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "overrides",
              "where": {"field": "gl_code"},
              "relate": "corrected_value"
            },
            "endpoint": "relate",
            "displayMode": "playground",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Anomaly Detection",
      "description": "Inverse prediction: low confidence = anomaly signal",
      "widgets": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "title": "How it works",
          "size": "full",
          "config": {
            "content": "## Anomaly Detection\n\nSame `_predict` engine, used in reverse. If Aito is confident about the GL code (high $p), the invoice fits known patterns. If confidence is low, something is unusual — that's the anomaly signal.\n\n**No separate anomaly model needed.** Compare the two queries below: known vendor vs unknown vendor."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Normal invoice: Kesko Oyj (high confidence = no anomaly)",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Kesko Oyj", "amount": 4220, "category": "supplies"},
              "predict": "gl_code",
              "select": ["$p", "feature"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "fixed",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "query",
          "title": "Anomalous: unknown vendor (low confidence = anomaly)",
          "size": "medium",
          "config": {
            "query": {
              "from": "invoices",
              "where": {"vendor": "Brand New Corp", "amount": 45000},
              "predict": "gl_code",
              "select": ["$p", "feature"]
            },
            "endpoint": "predict",
            "displayMode": "fixed",
            "outputFormat": "table",
            "runPolicy": "manual"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
